</div></div></section></section><section id="S13"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">PSAV curves across age, race and study groups</h3>
<p id="P25"><a href="#T4" class="usa-link">Tables 4.a and 4.b</a> show PSA rate of change and annual percent PSA at one year prior to diagnosis/exit. These rates are illustrated for all study groups, stratified by age and race and adjusted for baseline distribution of BMI and initial PSA value of 1.3 ng/ml. After the CP and at one year prior to diagnosis/exit, the absolute PSA rate among men in the high-risk cancer group appears to be significantly greater compared to no cancer and low-risk groups. The annual percent rate is higher among men who developed PrCA, but the differences between high and low-risk groups were smaller.</p>
